parts":[[2021]]},"DOI":"10.3390/ijms22020634","container-title":"International Journal of Molecular Sciences","abstract":"Medicinal mushrooms have important health benefits and exhibit a broad spectrum of pharmacological activities, including antiallergic, antibacterial, antifungal, anti-inflammatory, antioxidative, antiviral, cytotoxic, immunomodulating, antidepressive, antihyperlipidemic, antidiabetic, digestive, hepatoprotective, neuroprotective, nephroprotective, osteoprotective, and hypotensive activities. The growing interest in mycotherapy requires a strong commitment from the scientific community to expand clinical trials and to propose supplements of safe origin and genetic purity. Bioactive compounds of selected medicinal mushrooms and their effects and mechanisms in in vitro and in vivo clinical studies are reported in this review. Besides, we analyzed the therapeutic use and pharmacological activities of mushrooms.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Venturella","given":"Giuseppe","literal":""},{"family":"Venturella","given":"Giuseppe","literal":""},{"family":"Ferraro","given":"Valeria","literal":""},{"family":"Ferraro","given":"Valeria","literal":""},{"family":"Cirlincione","given":"Fortunato","literal":""},{"family":"Cirlincione","given":"Fortunato","literal":""},{"family":"Gargano","given":"Maria Letizia","literal":""},{"family":"Gargano","given":"Maria Letizia","literal":""},{"family":"Gargano","given":"Maria Letizia","literal":""}],"citation-key":"venturella_medicinal_2021","year":"2021","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Medicinal Mushrooms: Bioactive Compounds, Use, and Clinical Trials"],"author-links":["[[Author/Giuseppe Venturella]]","[[Author/Giuseppe Venturella]]","[[Author/Valeria Ferraro]]","[[Author/Valeria Ferraro]]","[[Author/Fortunato Cirlincione]]","[[Author/Fortunato Cirlincione]]","[[Author/Maria Letizia Gargano]]","[[Author/Maria Letizia Gargano]]","[[Author/Maria Letizia Gargano]]"],"atta